I am coding a custom Android soft keyboard app. In the settings page of the app, there is a SeekBar that resizes the height of the keyboard.

I am encountering a bug where, when the keyboard is downsized, the keys shrink as expected but the keyboard does not drop down to the bottom of the screen. There is no bug when the keyboard grows in size.

In the input method service's `onStartInputView`, I have the following:

```java
  @Override
  public void onStartInputView(final EditorInfo editorInfo, final boolean isRestarting)
  {
    super.onStartInputView(editorInfo, isRestarting);

    for (final Keyboard keyboard : keyboardSet)
    {
      keyboard.adjustKeyboardHeight();
    }
    inputContainer.updateHeight();
    // etc.
  }
```

* `keyboard.adjustKeyboardHeight()` applies a multiplier to the y-directional variables of each key.
* `inputContainer.updateHeight()` calls `requestLayout()`on the View the holds the keyboard and its keys.
* `inputContainer` is a FrameLayout containing the keyboard view (among other things).

Why isn't the `requestLayout` call sufficient to reposition the keyboard? How do I programmatically force the keyboard to be repositioned at the bottom of the screen?

One possible solution to the issue could be to add a `OnLayoutChangeListener` to the `inputContainer` view in the `onStartInputView` method. This listener will be called when the view layout changes, allowing for the keyboard to be repositioned properly.

Here's an example of how this could be implemented:

```java
  @Override
  public void onStartInputView(final EditorInfo editorInfo, final boolean isRestarting)
  {
    super.onStartInputView(editorInfo, isRestarting);

    for (final Keyboard keyboard : keyboardSet)
    {
      keyboard.adjustKeyboardHeight();
    }
    inputContainer.updateHeight();

    // Add a OnLayoutChangeListener to reposition the keyboard
    inputContainer.addOnLayoutChangeListener(new View.OnLayoutChangeListener() {
        @Override
        public void onLayoutChange(View v, int left, int top, int right, int bottom, int oldLeft,
                int oldTop, int oldRight, int oldBottom) {
            // Check if the bottom of the view has changed
            if (bottom != oldBottom) {
                // Post the repositioning of the keyboard to the UI thread
                v.post(new Runnable() {
                    @Override
                    public void run() {
                        // Get the window height and set the keyboard to the bottom
                        int screenHeight = getWindow().getDecorView().getHeight();
                        inputContainer.setY(screenHeight - inputContainer.getHeight());
                    }
                });
            }
        }
    });
  }
```

This code listens for layout changes to the `inputContainer` view and, when the bottom of the view changes, it posts a task on the UI thread to reposition the keyboard to the bottom of the screen using the `setY` method. The `getWindow().getDecorView().getHeight()` call gets the height of the entire screen including any system bars.

