To post a `Runnable` for an object being drawn, you can use the `post(Runnable)` method on the view that includes the object being drawn. 

For example, if you have a custom `View` that includes a drawable object that you need to update, you can use `post(Runnable)` to update the drawable object after the view's layout has been fully updated:

```java
public class MyCustomView extends View {
