In this example, a `Runnable` called `postRequestLayout` is defined that calls `inputContainer.requestLayout()` when executed. This `Runnable` is then posted to the message queue using `postOnAnimation(Runnable)`.

Alternatively, you can use the `ViewTreeObserver.OnPreDrawListener` interface to listen for the next draw pass and run a `Runnable` before the view is drawn. Here's an example:

```java
// create an OnPreDrawListener instance
