```

This code creates an instance of `ViewTreeObserver.OnPreDrawListener` and implements its `onPreDraw()` method, which is called before the view is drawn. In `onPreDraw()`, the `preDrawListener` instance removes itself from the view tree observer and calls `inputContainer.requestLayout()`. Then it returns `true` to indicate that the draw should proceed. Finally, `preDrawListener` is added to the view tree observer using `addOnPreDrawListener()`. 

Using `ViewTreeObserver.OnPreDrawListener` allows you to run a `Runnable` before the view is drawn, while still being able to get called before the view is drawn, without having to delay your request.

